//! TSCII (Tamil) <-> Unicode tables, generated byte-exact from host glibc
//! iconv(3). TSCII is a single-byte VISUAL-ORDER codec: 63 byte values
//! decode to 2-4 code points, and the preposed vowels E/EE/AI (0xa6/a7/a8)
//! reorder AFTER the following consonant. Decode uses a pending-vowel state
//! machine; encode is maximal-munch over the code-point stream where each
//! consonant+vowel sequence maps to its (reordered) byte string. 100% safe Rust.

